</IndexTerm><IndexTerm>
<Primary SortAs="previous button:on mailbox window">Previous button:on Mailbox window</Primary>
</IndexTerm><IndexTerm>
<Primary SortAs="reply to sender button:on mailbox window">Reply to Sender button:on Mailbox window</Primary>
</IndexTerm><IndexTerm>
<Primary SortAs="print button:on mailbox window">Print button:on Mailbox window</Primary>
</IndexTerm><IndexTerm>
<Primary>printing messages</Primary>
</IndexTerm><IndexTerm>
<Primary>messages, printing</Primary>
</IndexTerm>
&newline;&empty;
</Para>
<Graphic Entityref="MButtons" Id="HMLR.REF.fig.3"></Graphic>
<Para>The Mailbox buttons offer an alternative to using the pull-down
menus for common functions.</Para>
<VariableList>
<VarListEntry>
<Term><Emphasis Role="heading">Button</Emphasis></Term>
<ListItem>
<Para><Emphasis Role="heading">Function</Emphasis></Para>
</ListItem>
</VarListEntry>
<VarListEntry>
<Term>Delete</Term>
<ListItem>
<Para>Deletes the selected message from the mailbox. There is a equivalent menu
item in the Message menu.
</Para>
</ListItem>
</VarListEntry>
<VarListEntry>
<Term>Next</Term>
<ListItem>
<Para>Displays the message that follows the currently selected one.
There is a equivalent menu item in the View menu.</Para>
</ListItem>
</VarListEntry>
<VarListEntry>
<Term>Previous</Term>
<ListItem>
<Para>Displays the message that precedes the currently selected one.
There is an equivalent menu item in the View menu.</Para>
</ListItem>
</VarListEntry>
<VarListEntry>
<Term>Reply to Sender</Term>
<ListItem>
<Para>Automatically opens a Compose window with the sender's
address and the subject of the message filled in. There is an
equivalent menu item in the Compose menu.</Para>
</ListItem>
</VarListEntry>
<VarListEntry>
<Term>Print</Term>
<ListItem>
<Para>Prints the selected message(s). There is an equivalent menu item
in the Message menu.
</Para>
</ListItem>
</VarListEntry>
</VariableList>
